  "text": "The Kafka Streams topology build process follows this execution chain:\n\n1. **StreamsBuilder.build()** (StreamsBuilder.java:594-597): The public entry point that calls internalStreamsBuilder.buildAndOptimizeTopology(props) to trigger the topology compilation.\n\n2. **InternalStreamsBuilder.buildAndOptimizeTopology()** (InternalStreamsBuilder.java:308-337): This method orchestrates the topology optimization by:\n   - Calling mergeDuplicateSourceNodes() to consolidate redundant sources\n   - Calling optimizeTopology(props) to apply optimization rules (REUSE_KTABLE_SOURCE_TOPICS, MERGE_REPARTITION_TOPICS, SINGLE_STORE_SELF_JOIN)\n   - Iterating through the GraphNode tree using a priority queue\n   - For each graph node, calling writeToTopology(internalTopologyBuilder) which populates the InternalTopologyBuilder with processor definitions\n\n3. **InternalTopologyBuilder** (InternalTopologyBuilder.java): This class accumulates topology definitions through:\n   - nodeFactories: A LinkedHashMap of NodeFactory instances in topological order\n   - stateFactories: A map of StoreFactory instances for state stores\n   - globalStateBuilders and globalStateStores: For global state store management\n   - Various maps tracking source topics, sink topics, and state store connections\n\n4. **NodeFactory Hierarchy** (InternalTopologyBuilder.java:231-397): Includes:\n   - **ProcessorNodeFactory** (line 246): For processor nodes with optional state store connections\n   - **SourceNodeFactory** (line 297): For source nodes consuming from Kafka topics\n   - **SinkNodeFactory** (line 359): For sink nodes writing to Kafka topics\n   Each factory implements build() to create ProcessorNode instances\n\n5. **InternalTopologyBuilder.buildTopology()** (InternalTopologyBuilder.java:963-973): Public method that calls build(allNodes) to construct the processor topology.\n\n6. **InternalTopologyBuilder.build()** (InternalTopologyBuilder.java:1012-1060): The private build method that:\n   - Iterates through all NodeFactory instances in topological order\n   - Calls factory.build() on each to create ProcessorNode instances\n   - Routes ProcessorNodeFactory to buildProcessorNode()\n   - Routes SourceNodeFactory to buildSourceNode()\n   - Routes SinkNodeFactory to buildSinkNode()\n   - Creates and returns a ProcessorTopology with all constructed components\n\n7. **InternalTopologyBuilder.buildProcessorNode()** (InternalTopologyBuilder.java:1118-1158): For each processor node:\n   - Iterates through its required state store names\n   - Retrieves the corresponding StoreFactory from stateFactories\n   - Calls storeFactory.builder().build() to instantiate the StateStore\n   - Records changelog topic mappings if logging is enabled\n   - Adds the StateStore instance to the stateStoreMap\n\n8. **StoreFactory.builder()** (StoreFactory.java:51): Returns a StoreBuilder instance that was previously registered.\n\n9. **StoreBuilder.build()** (StoreBuilder.java:62): The final build method that creates the actual StateStore instance with configured caching and logging.\n\n10. **ProcessorTopology Constructor** (ProcessorTopology.java:49-77): Aggregates all components:\n   - processorNodes: List of ProcessorNode instances\n   - sourceNodesByTopic: Map of SourceNode instances by topic\n   - sinksByTopic: Map of SinkNode instances by sink topic\n   - stateStores: List of StateStore instances\n   - globalStateStores: List of global StateStore instances\n   - storeToChangelogTopic: Mapping for changelog topics\n   - repartitionTopics: Set of internal repartition topics\n\n11. **StreamTask Constructor** (StreamTask.java:123-147): Receives the ProcessorTopology and stores it for runtime use.\n\n12. **StreamTask.initializeTopology()** (StreamTask.java:1080-1091): During task initialization:\n   - Iterates through topology.processors() to get all ProcessorNode instances\n   - Calls node.init(processorContext, processingExceptionHandler) on each processor\n   - This initializes the processor's state stores and prepares it for record processing\n\nThe key interaction points are:\n- StoreBuilder registration occurs when StreamsBuilder.addStateStore() is called, wrapping the builder in StoreBuilderWrapper\n- Store instantiation happens lazily during ProcessorTopology.build() in buildProcessorNode()\n- Processor node initialization occurs when StreamTask.initializeTopology() is called before the task begins processing records\n- The entire topology is deterministically ordered through nodeFactories which maintains the order of addition"
